      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "One of the strongest philosophical arguments supporting your position is the concept of \"nozickian property rights,\" proposed by Robert Nozick. They argue that individuals have a natural right to their property (online content and freedoms) unencumbered by the state, unless their actions infringe on others' rights or harm society. This perspective asserts that government regulations can be seen as trespassing on individuals' autonomy and property rights. \n\nAdditionally, the ideas of libertarian philosopher John Locke also resonate with this argument, as he believed in the protection of natural rights, such as \"life, liberty, and property,\" unfettered by government interference.",
