      "content": "The concept of \"natural rights\" can be particularly pertinent to digital data and online communication due to the rapid evolution and fluidity of the internet. Unlike customary or state-granted rights, which have traditionally been tied to physical spaces, digital platforms can evolve and blur boundaries, leaving individuals' rights potentially unprotected.\n\nIn the digital sphere, the permanent, uncontrolled, and global nature of information and communication amplifies the idea of uninterrupted natural rights. Once shared online, data and speech can't be easily erased or confined, thus putting the state in a difficult position of regulating a rapidly changing, technically-defined property space.",
